to live a normal life.

03:44.307 --> 03:46.351
Well, you don't have
to go to meetings

03:46.351 --> 03:48.019
every single day, Samantha.

03:48.019 --> 03:50.355
Yes.
Unfortunately, I do.

03:50.355 --> 03:53.191
And so do most of the people
that I've dated recently.

03:53.191 --> 03:55.026
Which is why he is so exciting.

03:55.026 --> 03:57.696
Like, I know what my shit is,
you know, but what's his shit?

03:57.696 --> 03:59.364
What is his shit?

03:59.364 --> 04:02.701
I don't know.
It's probably not that bad.

04:02.701 --> 04:05.245
Well, you can never really know
a person, though, can you?

04:05.245 --> 04:06.746
BOB:
You know, your mom's not wrong.

04:06.746 --> 04:08.582
It wouldn't be the worst thing
in the world

04:08.582 --> 04:10.333
if you carried a little
pepper spray with you.

04:10.333 --> 04:12.252
You know,
when I was in Ecuador--

04:12.252 --> 04:14.337
this had to be like 15,
20 years ago...

04:14.337 --> 04:16.423
- Bob?
- Real quick.

04:16.423 --> 04:18.300
I was big in the
anarcho-environmentalist scene.

04:18.300 --> 04:21.470
What I didn't realize, though,
was that the cartels

04:21.470 --> 04:23.388
were targeting
the oil company protestors.

04:23.388 --> 04:24.848
So, when we fly down there,

04:24.848 --> 04:26.808
and I'm with,
I'm with Squirrel and Jerry...

04:26.808 --> 04:27.976
Okay, what's happening?

04:27.976 --> 04:29.311
'Cause my Uber's almost here,
so I need to...

04:29.311 --> 04:31.897
- He is driving me crazy.
- Mm-hmm.

04:31.897 --> 04:35.317
He recorded <i>Guy's Grocery Games</i>
on my DVR.

04:35.317 --> 04:37.027
- So what?
- So...

04:37.027 --> 04:38.612
he deleted my Swedish mystery.

04:38.612 --> 04:41.364
Now, I don't know
how <i>Jordskott</i> ends.

04:41.364 --> 04:44.451
I cannot escape him.
He's always here

04:44.451 --> 04:46.453
- playing his stupid guitar.
- Okay.

04:46.453 --> 04:48.914
And why is his shirt
in my closet?

04:48.914 --> 04:51.208
He has a perfectly good wardrobe
down in the garage.

04:51.208 --> 04:53.752
Okay, Mom,
if he's bothering you this much,

04:53.752 --> 04:56.004
- maybe you should take a break.
- What do you mean?

04:56.004 --> 04:59.758
I mean, if it's not working
with Bob, then end it.

05:01.051 --> 05:03.136
Why would you say that?
Do you not want me to be happy?

05:03.136 --> 05:04.429
Yes, I want you to be happy.

05:04.429 --> 05:06.598
I'm saying, if you're not--
you--

05:06.598 --> 05:08.600
I'm trying to be supportive.

05:08.600 --> 05:10.936
Oh, well, there's supportive,
and there's undermining.

05:10.936 --> 05:12.896
And I need space.

05:12.896 --> 05:15.649
- I get it.
- (knocking)

05:15.649 --> 05:17.317
BOB: Hey, what are you guys
up to in there?

05:17.317 --> 05:18.735
(whispering):
Somebody kill me.

05:18.735 --> 05:21.238
- SAMANTHA: Okay.
- Why don't you kill me?

05:21.238 --> 05:23.365
(whispering):
Bob, she needs space.

05:23.365 --> 05:25.492
Oh, sp...
(clicks tongue)

05:25.492 --> 05:27.327
All right, that was
the context clue I was missing.

05:27.327 --> 05:29.412
Um, well, I'm gonna go
to the grocery store

05:29.412 --> 05:34.125
