of raisin, clove, and plum.

07:00.712 --> 07:02.464
- Um...
- (cork pops)

07:02.464 --> 07:04.382
Sorry, none for me, thank you,
I'm on antibiotics.

07:04.382 --> 07:06.801
Oh, I didn't know
you were si--

07:06.801 --> 07:08.637
We didn't have to go out
if you're sick.

07:08.637 --> 07:09.971
- I'm not. I'm not.
- ALEX: Oh.

07:09.971 --> 07:11.431
It's just day six.

07:11.431 --> 07:13.141
Day six of the course.

07:13.141 --> 07:15.060
You know, trying to be
a more responsible adult

07:15.060 --> 07:17.896
and finish the whole thing
for once in my life,

07:17.896 --> 07:19.939
you know what I mean?
It's like, you get the thing,

07:19.939 --> 07:21.650
and then you take it for two
days, and then you feel better,

07:21.650 --> 07:22.859
and then they just sit
in your drawer forever.

07:22.859 --> 07:23.777
And so, I'm just trying
this new thing where I--

07:23.777 --> 07:25.445
But you should have the wine.

07:25.445 --> 07:26.946
ALEX: I'll take some wine.
Yeah, I'm healthy.

07:26.946 --> 07:27.947
(both chuckle)

07:27.947 --> 07:30.617
I will have hers and mine.
(chuckles)

07:30.617 --> 07:32.786
- Perfect.
- (wine pouring)

07:32.786 --> 07:34.204
- ALEX: Thank you so much.
- SOMMELIER: You're welcome.

07:34.204 --> 07:35.080
- (Alex chuckles)
- (exhales)

