12:34.504 --> 12:37.674
I'm engaging with this,
and this.

12:37.674 --> 12:38.758
And good night.

12:38.758 --> 12:40.885
Great. Okay.

12:49.143 --> 12:50.228
(phone chimes)

13:01.698 --> 13:03.449
(exhales)

13:03.449 --> 13:04.993
(scoffs)

13:21.426 --> 13:23.928
(toilet flushing)

13:25.972 --> 13:28.099
(loud gurgling)

13:33.354 --> 13:34.814
FELICIA: So,
you told him you don't drink

13:34.814 --> 13:36.065
- because you're on antibiotics.
- Yes.

13:36.065 --> 13:37.817
But I didn't mean to do that.

13:37.817 --> 13:40.236
It just sort of fell
out of my mouth.

13:40.236 --> 13:41.821
You know, that's actually
pretty clever.

13:41.821 --> 13:43.656
What?
No, it's not, it's embarrassing.

13:43.656 --> 13:45.033
Now, I would have to, like,

13:45.033 --> 13:46.492
make it a whole thing
and tell him the truth.

13:46.492 --> 13:48.995
I mean, is it even worth
that awkward of a conversation?

13:48.995 --> 13:50.496
I mean, yeah,
if you care about him,

13:50.496 --> 13:51.664
you should tell him what's up.

13:51.664 --> 13:53.082
Are you sure?

13:53.082 --> 13:54.542
What would I even say?

13:54.542 --> 13:57.378
"Hey, Alex, thanks so much
for that wonderful date.

13:57.378 --> 13:59.964
"I'm an alcoholic,
but I lied to you about that,

13:59.964 --> 14:02.133
"because I'm an alcoholic.
And then I lied to you

14:02.133 --> 14:03.634
about my friend being dumped,
'cause I'm an alcoholic."

14:03.634 --> 14:05.803
I think lying
is for all the people.

14:06.804 --> 14:08.806
It's sort of our thing, though.

14:08.806 --> 14:10.433
There's even a term for it
in the program.

14:10.433 --> 14:13.519
- It's called "old behavior."
- Oh, my God, Sam, stop, okay?

14:13.519 --> 14:15.063
You don't own lying on a date.

14:15.063 --> 14:16.522
I've been lied to
by plenty of dudes.

14:16.522 --> 14:18.608
You alcoholics just think
you're all special.

14:18.608 --> 14:20.985
- We are special.
- Okay, look.

14:20.985 --> 14:22.862
Everybody makes mistakes.

14:22.862 --> 14:24.864
You just gotta own up to 'em
so you can sleep

14:24.864 --> 14:26.532
like you just took a Benadryl.

14:26.532 --> 14:27.867
Yeah.

14:29.702 --> 14:30.995
I still don't want to tell him.

14:30.995 --> 14:32.538
Oh, my God,
of course you don't.

14:32.538 --> 14:34.207
Who wants to do anything?

14:35.541 --> 14:37.376
There she is.

14:37.376 --> 14:38.878
Do you actually
need something this time?

14:38.878 --> 14:39.962
'Cause I'm sort of busy
working on that column.

14:39.962 --> 14:41.672
Man, I gotta tell you,
it is a shame

14:41.672 --> 14:43.883
I can't compliment
that cute coat.

14:43.883 --> 14:45.009
- Love it.
- (phone buzzing)

14:45.009 --> 14:46.677
Okay, what do you need,
Nathaniel?

14:46.677 --> 14:48.221
Just want to shoot the breeze.

14:51.766 --> 14:53.518
- Okay.
- All right.

14:53.518 --> 14:54.852
Little jam sesh.

14:54.852 --> 14:57.271
Nathaniel, listen.

14:57.271 --> 14:59.440
I am not the person for you
to shoot the breeze with, okay?

14:59.440 --> 15:02.527
I'm your employee,
and I'm trying to do good work.

15:02.527 --> 15:05.446
If you need to talk to somebody,
that's totally understandable.

15:05.446 --> 15:07.031
But just call your wife.

15:07.031 --> 15:08.407
You were always going on about

15:08.407 --> 15:09.909
how much you loved Karen
at Bzzzzzzzzzz,

15:09.909 --> 15:11.244
and how great
your communication was.

15:11.244 --> 15:12.453
So, communicate with her.

15:12.453 --> 15:14.413
Just don't do it with me, please.

15:14.413 --> 15:16.040
A-And please stop
calling me in here

15:16.040 --> 15:17.834
unless it's about
an assignment, okay?

15:17.834 --> 15:20.545
Uh, Kar-- Karen left me.

15:22.046 --> 15:24.132
- What?
- Uh, yeah, she's, uh...

15:24.132 --> 15:27.552
she's-she's currently being
reamed by a New York Yankee.

15:29.554 --> 15:32.056
- Oh.
- Yeah.

15:32.056 --> 15:34.892
That's awful, and I'm--
I'm really sorry.

15:34.892 --> 15:36.227
But I'm still not the person

15:36.227 --> 15:37.937
you should be talking to
about this, okay?

15:37.937 --> 15:40.857
Uh, I would say
you are the exact person

15:40.857 --> 15:42.608
that I should be talking to
about this.

15:42.608 --> 15:47.029
I don't know anyone else
whose life got screwed up so bad

15:47.029 --> 15:50.032
and then came out of it okay
and is thriving.

15:50.032 --> 15:52.243
- You're the perfect person
to talk to.
- Okay.

15:52.243 --> 15:53.911
Fine.

15:53.911 --> 15:55.454
(sighs)

15:58.374 --> 15:59.667
(sighs)

15:59.667 --> 16:02.086
Is he an important Yankee?

16:03.045 --> 16:04.463
Uh, it's Nestor Cortes.

16:05.673 --> 16:07.466
- Whew.
- Yeah.

16:07.466 --> 16:11.304
And you know,
I just thought taking this job,

16:11.304 --> 16:12.972
coming to Boston, I could have

16:12.972 --> 16:15.057
just, like, a fresh start.

16:15.057 --> 16:16.601
But, God, I hate it here.

16:16.601 --> 16:18.686
I just hate Boston.

16:18.686 --> 16:21.022
I hate "chowdah."

16:21.022 --> 16:24.150
It's warm fish juice.
It's a con, it's bullshit.

16:24.150 --> 16:26.861
But you know what,
none of that matters,

16:26.861 --> 16:29.655
because my wife left me
for a Yankee.

16:29.655 --> 16:31.032
Sorry.

16:31.032 --> 16:33.326
(sighs)

16:34.243 --> 16:36.329
(footsteps approaching)

16:37.830 --> 16:39.207
Hi.

16:40.583 --> 16:43.753
Are you feeling better about
that whole diary <i>meshugas?</i>

16:43.753 --> 16:45.671
- Sure.
- Yeah.

16:45.671 --> 16:47.632
Mm, see?

16:47.632 --> 16:50.092
Get some food in your belly,
a little time,

16:50.092 --> 16:52.803
gives you perspective,
and you can go on with your life

16:52.803 --> 16:56.974
and just let go of all
that stuff that you read, oof.

16:58.309 --> 17:00.394
(whispering):
I'm not gonna do that, Bob.

17:07.360 --> 17:09.320
♪ ♪

17:12.365 --> 17:14.033
(exhales)

17:16.535 --> 17:17.828
Oh.

17:17.828 --> 17:19.288
- Hey.
- Hey.

17:19.288 --> 17:21.374
Um, I didn't know
you were gonna come by.

17:21.374 --> 17:22.959
I would have wore hard pants.

17:22.959 --> 17:25.336
- Oh.
- You know. Please, come in.

17:25.336 --> 17:27.004
Thanks.

17:30.383 --> 17:31.384
Wow.

17:31.384 --> 17:34.971
Really don't have, uh,
much stuff, huh?

17:34.971 --> 17:36.180
Yeah, it's kinda weird, right?

17:36.180 --> 17:38.975
Do you, like, murder people?

17:38.975 --> 17:40.518
No, my parents moved around
a lot,

17:40.518 --> 17:42.478
so I learned not to get
attached to things.

17:42.478 --> 17:43.604
- Huh.
- Yeah.

17:43.604 --> 17:46.190
Where do you keep your change,
or your keys?

17:46.190 --> 17:47.900
I can't tell you that
until we get closer.

17:47.900 --> 17:49.026
- Right.
- Yeah.

17:49.026 --> 17:50.903
- Right.
- Come on, come sit down.

17:50.903 --> 17:52.822
Oh, yeah.

17:55.116 --> 17:56.742
- You all right?
- I'm gonna stand.

17:56.742 --> 17:58.744
Okay. Should I stand?

17:58.744 --> 18:00.246
- No, you can sit.
- Okay.

18:00.246 --> 18:03.124
Um, so I just, uh, came here
to tell you something,

18:03.124 --> 18:04.834
and I'm just gonna tell you.

18:04.834 --> 18:06.836
I lied to you.

18:06.836 --> 18:09.046
I am not on antibiotics,

18:09.046 --> 18:10.965
I'm actually
a recovering alcoholic.

18:10.965 --> 18:12.717
That's why I don't drink.

18:12.717 --> 18:14.260
I don't know why
I didn't just tell you that.

18:14.260 --> 18:15.928
I should have.
It's not something

18:15.928 --> 18:17.847
that I'm, like, ashamed of
or anything.

18:17.847 --> 18:18.931
I mean, I used to be,

18:18.931 --> 18:20.891
but I don't think
that I am anymore.

18:20.891 --> 18:22.435
Also, my friend
didn't get dumped.

18:22.435 --> 18:24.061
I don't know why
I said that either.

18:24.061 --> 18:28.065
But... I'm sorry that I lied,

18:28.065 --> 18:31.527
and I'm sorry I'm so much.

18:31.527 --> 18:33.321
I really wish that I wasn't.

18:34.822 --> 18:36.324
I really like you,

18:36.324 --> 18:38.409
and I've really liked
getting to know you.

18:38.409 --> 18:41.954
And so, I hope that
you have a very nice life.

18:41.954 --> 18:43.539
And, uh, goodbye.

18:43.539 --> 18:45.166
Whoa, whoa, whoa,
whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

18:45.166 --> 18:47.251
What are you doing?
Where are you going?

18:47.251 --> 18:49.503
I-- I don't give a shit
about any of that.

18:49.503 --> 18:53.466
Well, I care that
you got healthy

18:53.466 --> 18:55.551
and you stopped drinking, but...

18:56.802 --> 18:59.388
I like you, and I don't think
you're too much.

18:59.388 --> 19:02.099
And we can still
smoke weed, right?

19:02.099 --> 19:05.436
No, I-- I don't do that either, actually.

19:05.436 --> 19:08.731
That's a bit of a bummer,
but we'll get past that, right?

19:09.815 --> 19:11.609
Can you sit down?

19:13.027 --> 19:15.154
Okay.

19:17.657 --> 19:19.492
You all right?

19:21.035 --> 19:25.164
So, you just want to, like,
keep seeing each other?

19:26.207 --> 19:27.541
Yeah.

19:29.627 --> 19:30.795
(chuckles)

19:30.795 --> 19:32.922
You're the weirdest person
I've ever met.

19:32.922 --> 19:34.965
Thank you.

19:34.965 --> 19:36.801
Good job
taking a compliment.

19:36.801 --> 19:38.219
You taught me well.

19:43.974 --> 19:45.267
Yes!

19:45.267 --> 19:46.519
(both laughing)

19:46.519 --> 19:49.188
- That was dope!
- (laughing)

19:58.030 --> 19:59.365
(sighs)

20:04.412 --> 20:06.622
I can't do it. I can't.

20:06.622 --> 20:07.873
I can't do it.

20:07.873 --> 20:10.167
- You can.
- Oh, damn it.

20:10.167 --> 20:12.044
This is how
you're gonna move on.

20:12.044 --> 20:14.171
I want to wipe my ass with this.

20:14.171 --> 20:15.506
I know.

20:17.007 --> 20:18.634
I want to just grab it,

20:18.634 --> 20:21.512
I want to go back to front,
and then piss on it.

20:21.512 --> 20:23.305
I know.

20:23.305 --> 20:24.807
You have to put it on.

20:27.226 --> 20:29.061
(sighing): Oh, man.

20:29.061 --> 20:31.147
(groans)

20:31.147 --> 20:32.648
Oh, my God.

20:32.648 --> 20:34.900
Oh, God.

20:34.900 --> 20:37.278
That just feels wrong.

20:38.237 --> 20:39.280
(Nathaniel sighs)

20:39.280 --> 20:40.990
You look... foxy.

20:43.284 --> 20:44.618
I know you're lying.

20:44.618 --> 20:45.995
I am.

20:45.995 --> 20:48.164
- But thank you.
- You're welcome.

